  "prompt": "Can I glue a tooth filling back into my mouth?",
  "response": "If a dental filling has come loose or fallen out, it's not advisable to attempt to glue it back in yourself. Using household adhesives can introduce harmful substances into your mouth and may lead to further complications or infections. Instead, it\u2019s best to contact your dentist as soon as possible. They can properly assess the situation and replace or repair the filling safely and effectively. In the meantime, you can manage any discomfort by avoiding very hot, cold, or sweet foods, and practicing good oral hygiene.",
